# Design Document: Real-Time Chat System

## Overview

The Real-Time Chat System is a WebSocket-based communication feature that enables users to engage in live conversations within the Vice City Dashboard. The system builds upon the existing WebSocket infrastructure (`wsClient`) and integrates with the authentication service to provide a seamless, real-time messaging experience.

### Key Features

- **Real-time messaging**: Instant message delivery with sub-200ms latency
- **Connection resilience**: Automatic reconnection with exponential backoff and message queuing
- **User presence tracking**: Live updates of online users in chat rooms
- **Typing indicators**: Visual feedback when users are composing messages
- **Message validation**: Client-side validation and sanitization to prevent XSS attacks
- **Rate limiting**: Spam prevention with configurable limits
- **Message history**: Load last 50 messages when joining a room
- **Accessibility**: Full keyboard navigation and screen reader support
- **Vice City aesthetic**: Neon-themed UI with glassmorphism effects

### Design Goals

1. **Reliability**: Handle network interruptions gracefully with automatic reconnection and message queuing
2. **Performance**: Maintain 60 FPS rendering even with high message volumes through virtualization
3. **Security**: Validate and sanitize all user input to prevent XSS and injection attacks
4. **Usability**: Provide clear feedback for all user actions and system states
5. **Accessibility**: Meet WCAG 2.1 Level AA standards for keyboard navigation and screen readers
6. **Scalability**: Support 500+ messages in memory with efficient rendering

## Architecture

### System Architecture

The chat system follows a client-server architecture with WebSocket communication:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                     Client (Browser)                         │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                               │
│  ┌──────────────┐      ┌──────────────┐                     │
│  │ ChatSystem   │◄────►│ UI_Component │                     │
│  │ (Container)  │      │ (Presenter)  │                     │
│  └──────┬───────┘      └──────────────┘                     │
│         │                                                     │
│         ├──────────┬──────────┬──────────┬──────────┐       │
│         ▼          ▼          ▼          ▼          ▼       │
│  ┌──────────┐ ┌────────┐ ┌────────┐ ┌────────┐ ┌────────┐ │
│  │Connection│ │Message │ │User    │ │Rate    │ │Message │ │
│  │Manager   │ │Manager │ │Presence│ │Limiter │ │Validator│ │
│  └────┬─────┘ └────────┘ └────────┘ └────────┘ └────────┘ │
│       │                                                       │
│       ▼                                                       │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│  │         WebSocket_Client (Existing)                   │   │
│  │         - Connection management                       │   │
│  │         - Event handling                              │   │
│  │         - Message queuing                             │   │
│  └────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘   │
│                            │                                  │
└────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────┘
                             │ WebSocket (Socket.IO)
                             │
┌────────────────────────────▼──────────────────────────────────┐
│                     Server (Backend)                          │
├───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐       │
│  │ WebSocket    │  │ Chat Room    │  │ Message      │       │
│  │ Handler      │  │ Manager      │  │ Store        │       │
│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘       │
└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Component Responsibilities

#### ChatSystem (Container Component)
- Orchestrates all chat functionality
- Manages component lifecycle (mount/unmount)
- Coordinates between sub-components
- Handles room join/leave operations
- Manages React state for messages, users, and connection status

#### Connection_Manager
- Manages WebSocket connection lifecycle
- Implements exponential backoff reconnection strategy
- Tracks connection status (connected, disconnected, reconnecting, failed)
- Handles authentication token management
- Triggers token refresh when expiry is near

#### Message_Manager
- Stores and manages chat messages in memory
- Enforces 500-message cache limit
- Merges real-time messages with history
- Prevents duplicate message display using message ID tracking
- Handles message ordering by timestamp and ID

#### Message_Validator
- Validates message length (1-500 characters)
- Trims whitespace and checks for empty messages
- Escapes HTML special characters to prevent XSS
- Validates line breaks (max 10)
- Checks for invalid control characters

#### Rate_Limiter
- Implements sliding window rate limiting (5 messages per 10 seconds)
- Prevents duplicate message spam (2-second cooldown)
- Tracks message timestamps and content
- Provides clear error messages with wait times

#### User_Presence_Tracker
- Maintains list of online users in current room
- Handles user join/leave events
- Implements 30-second timeout for disconnected users
- Supports multiple connections per user

#### UI_Component
- Renders chat interface with Vice City aesthetic
- Displays messages with timestamps and avatars
- Shows typing indicators and online user count
- Implements auto-scroll behavior
- Provides keyboard navigation and ARIA labels

### Data Flow

#### Sending a Message

```
User Input → Message_Validator → Rate_Limiter → Connection_Manager → 
WebSocket_Client → Server → Broadcast → All Clients → UI_Component
```

1. User types message and presses Enter
2. Message_Validator validates and sanitizes content
3. Rate_Limiter checks if message is allowed
4. Connection_Manager checks connection status
5. If connected: WebSocket_Client emits message
6. If disconnected: Message_Queue stores message
7. Server receives and broadcasts to all room participants
8. All clients receive broadcast and update UI

#### Receiving a Message

```
Server Broadcast → WebSocket_Client → Message_Manager → 
UI_Component → Render
```

1. Server broadcasts message to all room participants
2. WebSocket_Client receives message event
3. Message_Manager adds to message list (checks for duplicates)
4. UI_Component re-renders with new message
5. Auto-scroll triggers if user is near bottom

#### Connection Recovery

```
Disconnect → Connection_Manager → Exponential Backoff → 
Reconnect → Flush Message_Queue → Request History
```

1. WebSocket disconnect event detected
2. Connection_Manager updates status to "disconnected"
3. Exponential backoff delays: 1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s
4. Reconnection attempt initiated
5. On success: Flush queued messages
6. Request message history to catch up

## Components and Interfaces

### ChatSystem Component

**Purpose**: Main container component that orchestrates all chat functionality.

**Props**:
```typescript
interface ChatSystemProps {
  roomId: string;           // Unique identifier for the chat room
  userId: string;           // Current authenticated user's ID
  username: string;         // Current authenticated user's username
  maxMessageLength?: number; // Maximum message length (default: 500)
}
```

**State**:
```typescript
interface ChatSystemState {
  messages: ChatMessage[];           // Array of chat messages
  inputMessage: string;              // Current input field value
  connectionStatus: ConnectionStatus; // Current connection state
  onlineUsers: string[];             // List of online user IDs
  typingUsers: Set<string>;          // Set of currently typing usernames
  error: ErrorState | null;          // Current error state
  isLoadingHistory: boolean;         // Message history loading state
  messageCache: Set<string>;         // Set of message IDs for deduplication
}
```

**Key Methods**:
- `handleSendMessage()`: Validates and sends a message
- `handleInputChange()`: Updates input and triggers typing indicator
- `handleJoinRoom()`: Joins a chat room and requests history
- `handleLeaveRoom()`: Leaves current room and cleans up
- `scrollToBottom()`: Auto-scrolls to latest message

### Message_Validator Module

**Purpose**: Validates and sanitizes message content before sending or displaying.

**Interface**:
```typescript
interface MessageValidator {
  validate(content: string): ValidationResult;
  sanitize(content: string): string;
}

interface ValidationResult {
  valid: boolean;
  sanitized: string;
  error?: string;
}
```

**Validation Rules**:
1. Trim leading/trailing whitespace
2. Check if empty after trimming
3. Check length (1-500 characters)
4. Count line breaks (max 10)
5. Check for null bytes and control characters
6. Escape HTML special characters

**Implementation**:
```typescript
class MessageValidatorImpl implements MessageValidator {
  private readonly MAX_LENGTH = 500;
  private readonly MAX_LINE_BREAKS = 10;
  
  validate(content: string): ValidationResult {
    // Step 1: Trim whitespace
    const trimmed = content.trim();
    
    // Step 2: Check empty
    if (trimmed.length === 0) {
      return {
        valid: false,
        sanitized: '',
        error: 'Message cannot be empty'
      };
    }
    
    // Step 3: Check length
    if (trimmed.length > this.MAX_LENGTH) {
      return {
        valid: false,
        sanitized: trimmed,
        error: `Message exceeds maximum length of ${this.MAX_LENGTH} characters`
      };
    }
    
    // Step 4: Check line breaks
    const lineBreaks = (trimmed.match(/\n/g) || []).length;
    if (lineBreaks > this.MAX_LINE_BREAKS) {
      return {
        valid: false,
        sanitized: trimmed,
        error: `Message exceeds maximum of ${this.MAX_LINE_BREAKS} lines`
      };
    }
    
    // Step 5: Check control characters
    if (/[\x00-\x08\x0B\x0C\x0E-\x1F]/.test(trimmed)) {
      return {
        valid: false,
        sanitized: trimmed,
        error: 'Message contains invalid characters'
      };
    }
    
    // Step 6: Sanitize
    const sanitized = this.sanitize(trimmed);
    
    return {
      valid: true,
      sanitized,
    };
  }
  
  sanitize(content: string): string {
    return content
      .replace(/&/g, '&amp;')
      .replace(/</g, '&lt;')
      .replace(/>/g, '&gt;')
      .replace(/"/g, '&quot;')
      .replace(/'/g, '&#x27;');
  }
}
```

### Rate_Limiter Module

**Purpose**: Prevents message spam through rate limiting and duplicate detection.

**Interface**:
```typescript
interface RateLimiter {
  canSendMessage(content: string): RateLimitResult;
  recordMessage(content: string, timestamp: number): void;
  cleanup(): void;
}

interface RateLimitResult {
  allowed: boolean;
  reason?: 'rate_limit' | 'duplicate';
  waitTime?: number; // seconds
}
```

**Implementation**:
```typescript
class RateLimiterImpl implements RateLimiter {
  private readonly MAX_MESSAGES = 5;
  private readonly WINDOW_MS = 10000; // 10 seconds
  private readonly DUPLICATE_COOLDOWN_MS = 2000; // 2 seconds
  
  private messageTimestamps: number[] = [];
  private lastMessage: { content: string; timestamp: number } | null = null;
  
  canSendMessage(content: string): RateLimitResult {
    const now = Date.now();
    
    // Clean up old timestamps
    this.messageTimestamps = this.messageTimestamps.filter(
      ts => now - ts < this.WINDOW_MS
    );
    
    // Check rate limit
    if (this.messageTimestamps.length >= this.MAX_MESSAGES) {
      const oldestTimestamp = this.messageTimestamps[0];
      const waitTime = Math.ceil((this.WINDOW_MS - (now - oldestTimestamp)) / 1000);
      return {
        allowed: false,
        reason: 'rate_limit',
        waitTime
      };
    }
    
    // Check duplicate
    if (this.lastMessage && 
        this.lastMessage.content === content &&
        now - this.lastMessage.timestamp < this.DUPLICATE_COOLDOWN_MS) {
      return {
        allowed: false,
        reason: 'duplicate',
        waitTime: Math.ceil((this.DUPLICATE_COOLDOWN_MS - (now - this.lastMessage.timestamp)) / 1000)
      };
    }
    
    return { allowed: true };
  }
  
  recordMessage(content: string, timestamp: number): void {
    this.messageTimestamps.push(timestamp);
    this.lastMessage = { content, timestamp };
  }
  
  cleanup(): void {
    this.messageTimestamps = [];
    this.lastMessage = null;
  }
}
```

### Connection_Manager Module

**Purpose**: Manages WebSocket connection lifecycle and authentication.

**Interface**:
```typescript
interface ConnectionManager {
  connect(token: string): Promise<void>;
  disconnect(): void;
  getStatus(): ConnectionStatus;
  onStatusChange(callback: (status: ConnectionStatus) => void): void;
  checkTokenExpiry(): Promise<void>;
}

type ConnectionStatus = 'connected' | 'disconnected' | 'reconnecting' | 'failed';
```

**Key Features**:
- Exponential backoff: 1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s
- Maximum 5 reconnection attempts
- Token refresh when expiry within 5 minutes
- Authentication error handling with redirect

### User_Presence_Tracker Module

**Purpose**: Tracks online users in the current chat room.

**Interface**:
```typescript
interface UserPresenceTracker {
  addUser(userId: string, username: string): void;
  removeUser(userId: string): void;
  getOnlineUsers(): OnlineUser[];
  getOnlineCount(): number;
}

interface OnlineUser {
  userId: string;
  username: string;
  joinedAt: Date;
  connectionIds: string[]; // Support multiple connections
}
```

**Key Features**:
- 30-second timeout for disconnected users
- Support for multiple connections per user
- Broadcast presence updates within 500ms

## Data Models

### ChatMessage

```typescript
interface ChatMessage {
  id: string;                    // Unique message identifier (UUID)
  roomId: string;                // Chat room identifier
  userId: string;                // Sender's user ID ('system' for system messages)
  username: string;              // Sender's username
  avatar?: string;               // Optional avatar URL
  content: string;               // Message content (sanitized)
  timestamp: Date;               // Server timestamp
  edited: boolean;               // Whether message was edited
  reactions: Reaction[];         // Array of reactions (future feature)
}
```

### Reaction

```typescript
interface Reaction {
  emoji: string;                 // Emoji character
  userIds: string[];             // Array of user IDs who reacted
  count: number;                 // Total reaction count
}
```

### ConnectionStatus

```typescript
type ConnectionStatus = 
  | 'connected'      // Successfully connected to server
  | 'disconnected'   // Not connected, attempting reconnection
  | 'reconnecting'   // Currently attempting to reconnect
  | 'failed';        // Max reconnection attempts reached
```

### ErrorState

```typescript
interface ErrorState {
  type: ErrorType;
  message: string;
  recoverable: boolean;
  retryAction?: () => void;
}

type ErrorType = 
  | 'validation'     // Message validation failed
  | 'rate_limit'     // Rate limit exceeded
  | 'network'        // Network error
  | 'authentication' // Auth error
  | 'connection'     // Connection error
  | 'server';        // Server error
```

### TypingIndicator

```typescript
interface TypingIndicator {
  userId: string;
  username: string;
  timestamp: number;  // When typing started
}
```

### MessageQueue

```typescript
interface QueuedMessage {
  event: string;
  data: {
    roomId: string;
    content: string;
  };
  timestamp: number;
}
```

### WebSocket Events

#### Client → Server

```typescript
// Join room
interface JoinRoomEvent {
  event: 'chat:join';
  data: {
    roomId: string;
  };
}

// Leave room
interface LeaveRoomEvent {
  event: 'chat:leave';
  data: {
    roomId: string;
  };
}

// Send message
interface SendMessageEvent {
  event: 'chat:message';
  data: {
    roomId: string;
    content: string;
  };
}

// Typing indicator
interface TypingEvent {
  event: 'chat:typing';
  data: {
    roomId: string;
    isTyping: boolean;
  };
}

// Request history
interface HistoryRequestEvent {
  event: 'chat:history';
  data: {
    roomId: string;
    limit: number;
  };
}
```

#### Server → Client

```typescript
// Message broadcast
interface MessageBroadcast {
  event: 'chat:message';
  data: ChatMessage;
}

// User joined
interface UserJoinedEvent {
  event: 'chat:user-joined';
  data: {
    userId: string;
    username: string;
  };
}

// User left
interface UserLeftEvent {
  event: 'chat:user-left';
  data: {
    userId: string;
    username: string;
  };
}

// Typing indicator
interface TypingBroadcast {
  event: 'chat:typing';
  data: {
    userId: string;
    username: string;
    isTyping: boolean;
  };
}

// Online users list
interface OnlineUsersEvent {
  event: 'chat:users';
  data: {
    users: string[];
  };
}

// Message history
interface HistoryResponse {
  event: 'chat:history';
  data: {
    messages: ChatMessage[];
  };
}

// Error
interface ErrorEvent {
  event: 'chat:error';
  data: {
    type: string;
    message: string;
  };
}
```



## Correctness Properties

*A property is a characteristic or behavior that should hold true across all valid executions of a system—essentially, a formal statement about what the system should do. Properties serve as the bridge between human-readable specifications and machine-verifiable correctness guarantees.*

### Property 1: Valid Message Acceptance

*For any* string with length between 1 and 500 characters that contains at least one non-whitespace character, has 10 or fewer line breaks, and contains no invalid control characters, the Message_Validator SHALL accept the message and return a sanitized version.

**Validates: Requirements 1.1, 6.1, 6.2, 6.3, 6.5, 6.6**

### Property 2: HTML Character Escaping

*For any* message containing HTML special characters (&, <, >, ", '), the Message_Validator SHALL escape all occurrences to their HTML entity equivalents (&amp;, &lt;, &gt;, &quot;, &#x27;) to prevent XSS attacks.

**Validates: Requirements 6.4**

### Property 3: Whitespace-Only Rejection

*For any* string composed entirely of whitespace characters (spaces, tabs, newlines, carriage returns, or any combination thereof), the Message_Validator SHALL reject the message with error "Message cannot be empty".

**Validates: Requirements 1.5, 6.3**

### Property 4: Length Boundary Enforcement

*For any* string, the Message_Validator SHALL accept messages with length ≤ 500 characters after trimming and SHALL reject messages with length > 500 characters with error "Message exceeds maximum length of 500 characters".

**Validates: Requirements 1.4, 6.1**

### Property 5: Line Break Limit Enforcement

*For any* message, the Message_Validator SHALL accept messages containing 10 or fewer line break characters (U+000A) and SHALL reject messages containing more than 10 line breaks with error "Message exceeds maximum of 10 lines".

**Validates: Requirements 6.5**

### Property 6: Control Character Rejection

*For any* message containing null bytes (U+0000) or control characters in the range U+0001 to U+001F (excluding U+000A line feed and U+000D carriage return), the Message_Validator SHALL reject the message with error "Message contains invalid characters".

**Validates: Requirements 6.6**

### Property 7: Chronological Message Ordering

*For any* array of ChatMessage objects, when sorted by the Chat_System display logic, messages SHALL be ordered by timestamp in ascending order, with ties broken by message ID in ascending lexicographic order.

**Validates: Requirements 1.9**

### Property 8: Rate Limit Sliding Window

*For any* sequence of message send attempts with timestamps, the Rate_Limiter SHALL allow at most 5 messages within any 10-second sliding window, rejecting additional attempts until the oldest message timestamp falls outside the window.

**Validates: Requirements 9.1, 9.2**

### Property 9: Duplicate Message Prevention

*For any* message content, if the same content was sent less than 2 seconds ago (based on timestamp comparison), the Rate_Limiter SHALL reject the duplicate message; if 2 or more seconds have elapsed, the Rate_Limiter SHALL allow the message.

**Validates: Requirements 9.5, 9.8**

### Property 10: Room ID Validation

*For any* string consisting only of alphanumeric characters (a-z, A-Z, 0-9) with length between 1 and 64 characters inclusive, the Chat_System SHALL accept it as a valid room ID and emit a join event.

**Validates: Requirements 3.1, 3.11**

### Property 11: Validation Order Consistency

*For any* message input, the Message_Validator SHALL execute validation steps in the following order: (1) trim whitespace, (2) check empty, (3) check length, (4) check line breaks, (5) check control characters, (6) escape HTML, returning the first error encountered or the sanitized message if all checks pass.

**Validates: Requirements 6.12**

### Property 12: Message Deduplication by ID

*For any* set of ChatMessage objects with unique IDs, when merged into the message list, the Message_Manager SHALL ensure each message ID appears at most once in the displayed message list, preventing duplicate display.

**Validates: Requirements 11.5, 11.6**

## Error Handling

### Error Categories

The chat system handles errors in the following categories:

#### 1. Validation Errors

**Trigger**: User input fails validation rules
**Handling**:
- Display inline error message below input field
- Retain message content in input field
- Clear error after 5 seconds or on successful send
- Do not send message to server

**Error Messages**:
- "Message cannot be empty" - whitespace-only message
- "Message exceeds maximum length of 500 characters" - length > 500
- "Message exceeds maximum of 10 lines" - line breaks > 10
- "Message contains invalid characters" - null bytes or control characters

#### 2. Rate Limit Errors

**Trigger**: User exceeds rate limits
**Handling**:
- Display error message with wait time
- Retain message content in input field
- Clear error after wait time expires or on successful send
- Do not send message to server

**Error Messages**:
- "Rate limit exceeded. Please wait X seconds." - 5 messages in 10 seconds
- "Duplicate message detected. Please wait X seconds." - same content within 2 seconds

#### 3. Network Errors

**Trigger**: WebSocket send fails due to network issues
**Handling**:
- Display error notification for 3 seconds
- Retain message content in input field
- Provide retry button
- Log error to console

**Error Messages**:
- "Failed to send message. Please try again."

#### 4. Connection Errors

**Trigger**: WebSocket connection lost or fails
**Handling**:
- Update connection status indicator
- Disable message input field
- Queue outgoing messages (max 100)
- Attempt automatic reconnection with exponential backoff
- Display reconnection status

**Error Messages**:
- "Disconnected. Reconnecting..." - during reconnection attempts
- "Connection lost. Please refresh the page." - after 5 failed attempts
- "Unable to connect to chat server" - initial connection timeout (10s)
- "Message queue full - cannot send while disconnected" - queue exceeds 100

#### 5. Authentication Errors

**Trigger**: Invalid or expired authentication token
**Handling**:
- Display error message
- Attempt token refresh (3 retries with 1s delay)
- If refresh fails, redirect to login page after 2 seconds
- Include return URL for post-login redirect
- Do not provide retry button (automatic handling)

**Error Messages**:
- "Authentication required" - missing token
- "Authentication failed. Redirecting to login..." - invalid token or refresh failed

#### 6. Room Operation Errors

**Trigger**: Join/leave room operations fail
**Handling**:
- Display error message
- Provide retry button for join failures
- Log error for leave failures (non-blocking)
- Clear error after 5 seconds

**Error Messages**:
- "Failed to join room" - join timeout (5s)
- "Invalid room ID" - room ID validation failed
- "Failed to load message history" - history request timeout (3s)

#### 7. Server Errors

**Trigger**: Server returns error response
**Handling**:
- Display generic error message
- Log detailed error to console
- Provide retry button if recoverable
- Clear error after 5 seconds

**Error Messages**:
- "Server error. Please try again."

### Error Recovery Strategies

#### Automatic Recovery

1. **Connection Recovery**:
   - Exponential backoff: 1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s
   - Maximum 5 attempts
   - Flush message queue on reconnection
   - Request message history to catch up

2. **Token Refresh**:
   - Automatic refresh when expiry within 5 minutes
   - 3 retry attempts with 1s delay
   - Redirect to login if all attempts fail

3. **Message Queue**:
   - Store up to 100 messages while disconnected
   - Transmit in chronological order on reconnection
   - Clear queue on successful transmission

#### Manual Recovery

1. **Retry Button**:
   - Provided for network errors
   - Provided for room join failures
   - Provided for history load failures
   - Retries the failed operation

2. **Refresh Page**:
   - Suggested after max reconnection attempts
   - Suggested for persistent errors
   - Clears all state and re-initializes

### Error Logging

All errors are logged to the browser console with:
- Timestamp
- Error type
- Error message
- Error details (stack trace, context)
- User ID and room ID (if available)

**Log Format**:
```typescript
console.error('[Chat Error]', {
  timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
  type: errorType,
  message: errorMessage,
  details: errorDetails,
  userId: currentUserId,
  roomId: currentRoomId,
  stack: error.stack
});
```

### Error State Management

The chat system maintains a single error state to avoid overwhelming the user:

```typescript
interface ErrorState {
  type: ErrorType;
  message: string;
  recoverable: boolean;
  retryAction?: () => void;
  clearTimeout?: NodeJS.Timeout;
}
```

**Rules**:
- Only one error displayed at a time
- New errors replace previous errors
- Errors auto-clear after 5 seconds (except authentication errors)
- Successful actions immediately clear errors
- Non-recoverable errors do not provide retry button

## Testing Strategy

### Testing Approach

The Real-Time Chat System requires a comprehensive testing strategy that combines:

1. **Property-Based Tests**: Verify universal properties across all inputs
2. **Unit Tests**: Test specific behaviors and edge cases
3. **Integration Tests**: Test component interactions and WebSocket communication
4. **Accessibility Tests**: Verify WCAG 2.1 Level AA compliance

### Property-Based Testing

**Framework**: fast-check (TypeScript/JavaScript property-based testing library)

**Configuration**:
- Minimum 100 iterations per property test
- Each test tagged with feature name and property number
- Tag format: `Feature: real-time-chat-system, Property {number}: {property_text}`

**Property Tests**:

#### 1. Message Validation Properties

```typescript
// Property 1: Valid Message Acceptance
// Feature: real-time-chat-system, Property 1: Valid Message Acceptance
fc.assert(
  fc.property(
    fc.string({ minLength: 1, maxLength: 500 })
      .filter(s => s.trim().length > 0)
      .filter(s => (s.match(/\n/g) || []).length <= 10)
      .filter(s => !/[\x00-\x08\x0B\x0C\x0E-\x1F]/.test(s)),
    (message) => {
      const result = messageValidator.validate(message);
      expect(result.valid).toBe(true);
      expect(result.sanitized).toBeDefined();
    }
  ),
  { numRuns: 100 }
);

// Property 2: HTML Character Escaping
// Feature: real-time-chat-system, Property 2: HTML Character Escaping
fc.assert(
  fc.property(
    fc.string().filter(s => /[&<>"']/.test(s)),
    (message) => {
      const sanitized = messageValidator.sanitize(message);
      expect(sanitized).not.toContain('&');
      expect(sanitized).not.toContain('<');
      expect(sanitized).not.toContain('>');
      expect(sanitized).not.toContain('"');
      expect(sanitized).not.toContain("'");
      expect(sanitized).toContain('&amp;' || '&lt;' || '&gt;' || '&quot;' || '&#x27;');
    }
  ),
  { numRuns: 100 }
);

// Property 3: Whitespace-Only Rejection
// Feature: real-time-chat-system, Property 3: Whitespace-Only Rejection
fc.assert(
  fc.property(
    fc.array(fc.constantFrom(' ', '\t', '\n', '\r'), { minLength: 1 })
      .map(arr => arr.join('')),
    (whitespaceMessage) => {
      const result = messageValidator.validate(whitespaceMessage);
      expect(result.valid).toBe(false);
      expect(result.error).toBe('Message cannot be empty');
    }
  ),
  { numRuns: 100 }
);

// Property 4: Length Boundary Enforcement
// Feature: real-time-chat-system, Property 4: Length Boundary Enforcement
fc.assert(
  fc.property(
    fc.string(),
    (message) => {
      const result = messageValidator.validate(message);
      const trimmedLength = message.trim().length;
      
      if (trimmedLength === 0) {
        expect(result.valid).toBe(false);
      } else if (trimmedLength > 500) {
        expect(result.valid).toBe(false);
        expect(result.error).toContain('exceeds maximum length');
      } else {
        // May still fail other validations, but not length
        if (!result.valid) {
          expect(result.error).not.toContain('exceeds maximum length');
        }
      }
    }
  ),
  { numRuns: 100 }
);

// Property 5: Line Break Limit Enforcement
// Feature: real-time-chat-system, Property 5: Line Break Limit Enforcement
fc.assert(
  fc.property(
    fc.integer({ min: 0, max: 20 }),
    fc.string({ minLength: 1, maxLength: 100 }),
    (lineBreakCount, baseText) => {
      const message = baseText + '\n'.repeat(lineBreakCount);
      const result = messageValidator.validate(message);
      
      if (lineBreakCount > 10) {
        expect(result.valid).toBe(false);
        expect(result.error).toContain('exceeds maximum of 10 lines');
      } else if (message.trim().length > 0 && message.trim().length <= 500) {
        // May pass or fail other validations, but not line break limit
        if (!result.valid) {
          expect(result.error).not.toContain('exceeds maximum of 10 lines');
        }
      }
    }
  ),
  { numRuns: 100 }
);

// Property 6: Control Character Rejection
// Feature: real-time-chat-system, Property 6: Control Character Rejection
fc.assert(
  fc.property(
    fc.string({ minLength: 1, maxLength: 100 }),
    fc.integer({ min: 0x00, max: 0x1F }).filter(c => c !== 0x0A && c !== 0x0D),
    (baseText, controlChar) => {
      const message = baseText + String.fromCharCode(controlChar);
      const result = messageValidator.validate(message);
      expect(result.valid).toBe(false);
      expect(result.error).toBe('Message contains invalid characters');
    }
  ),
  { numRuns: 100 }
);
```

#### 2. Message Ordering Property

```typescript
// Property 7: Chronological Message Ordering
// Feature: real-time-chat-system, Property 7: Chronological Message Ordering
fc.assert(
  fc.property(
    fc.array(
      fc.record({
        id: fc.uuid(),
        timestamp: fc.date(),
        content: fc.string()
      }),
      { minLength: 2, maxLength: 50 }
    ),
    (messages) => {
      const sorted = messageManager.sortMessages(messages);
      
      for (let i = 1; i < sorted.length; i++) {
        const prev = sorted[i - 1];
        const curr = sorted[i];
        
        // Check timestamp ordering
        if (prev.timestamp.getTime() === curr.timestamp.getTime()) {
          // Tie-breaker: message ID ascending
          expect(prev.id.localeCompare(curr.id)).toBeLessThanOrEqual(0);
        } else {
          expect(prev.timestamp.getTime()).toBeLessThan(curr.timestamp.getTime());
        }
      }
    }
  ),
  { numRuns: 100 }
);
```

#### 3. Rate Limiting Properties

```typescript
// Property 8: Rate Limit Sliding Window
// Feature: real-time-chat-system, Property 8: Rate Limit Sliding Window
fc.assert(
  fc.property(
    fc.array(
      fc.record({
        content: fc.string({ minLength: 1, maxLength: 50 }),
        timestamp: fc.integer({ min: 0, max: 30000 }) // 30 seconds
      }),
      { minLength: 1, maxLength: 20 }
    ),
    (attempts) => {
      const rateLimiter = new RateLimiterImpl();
      const sortedAttempts = attempts.sort((a, b) => a.timestamp - b.timestamp);
      
      let allowedCount = 0;
      
      for (const attempt of sortedAttempts) {
        // Count messages in 10-second window before this attempt
        const windowStart = attempt.timestamp - 10000;
        const messagesInWindow = sortedAttempts.filter(
          a => a.timestamp >= windowStart && a.timestamp < attempt.timestamp
        ).length;
        
        const result = rateLimiter.canSendMessage(attempt.content);
        
        if (messagesInWindow < 5) {
          expect(result.allowed).toBe(true);
          if (result.allowed) {
            rateLimiter.recordMessage(attempt.content, attempt.timestamp);
            allowedCount++;
          }
        }
      }
    }
  ),
  { numRuns: 100 }
);

// Property 9: Duplicate Message Prevention
// Feature: real-time-chat-system, Property 9: Duplicate Message Prevention
fc.assert(
  fc.property(
    fc.string({ minLength: 1, maxLength: 100 }),
    fc.integer({ min: 0, max: 5000 }), // time delta in ms
    (content, timeDelta) => {
      const rateLimiter = new RateLimiterImpl();
      const firstTimestamp = 1000;
      const secondTimestamp = firstTimestamp + timeDelta;
      
      // Send first message
      rateLimiter.recordMessage(content, firstTimestamp);
      
      // Try to send duplicate
      const result = rateLimiter.canSendMessage(content);
      
      if (timeDelta < 2000) {
        expect(result.allowed).toBe(false);
        expect(result.reason).toBe('duplicate');
      } else {
        // May be allowed (unless rate limit hit)
        if (!result.allowed) {
          expect(result.reason).not.toBe('duplicate');
        }
      }
    }
  ),
  { numRuns: 100 }
);
```

